🔹 PART 1: WITHOUT MAC BINDING (Dynamic DHCP)
🔸 Step 1: Install dnsmasq (On Server)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install dnsmasq 


Check status:

sudo systemctl status dnsmasq

🔸 Step 2: Stop Services Before Configuration
sudo systemctl stop dnsmasq
sudo service network-manager stop

🔸 Step 3: Configure dnsmasq

Open config file:

sudo nano /etc/dnsmasq.conf

1️⃣ Set Interface

Search for:

#interface=


Uncomment and set your Ethernet name:

interface=enp0s25


(Use ip a to check your interface name)

2️⃣ Set DHCP Range

Search:

#dhcp-range=


Uncomment and set:

dhcp-range=192.168.0.6,192.168.0.50,255.255.255.0,12h


Save and exit (CTRL + X → Y → Enter)

🔸 Step 4: Assign Static IP to Server
sudo ifconfig enp0s25 192.168.0.5 netmask 255.255.255.0


Check:

ifconfig


Server IP should be:

192.168.0.5

🔸 Step 5: Restart Services
sudo service network-manager start
sudo systemctl start dnsmasq


Check status:

sudo systemctl status dnsmasq

🔸 Step 6: On Client Machine

Restart network or reboot client:

sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager


Check IP:

ifconfig


✅ Client IP should be between:

192.168.0.6 – 192.168.0.50

🔹 PART 2: WITH MAC BINDING (Static IP for Specific Client)
🔸 Step 1: Get Client MAC Address

On Client:

ip a


Example MAC:

18:60:24:89:cc:89

🔸 Step 2: Edit dnsmasq.conf (On Server)
sudo nano /etc/dnsmasq.conf


Search:

#dhcp-host=


Add this line:

dhcp-host=18:60:24:89:cc:89,192.168.0.10


👉 Format:

dhcp-host=MAC_ADDRESS,IP_ADDRESS


Save and exit.

🔸 Step 3: Restart dnsmasq
sudo systemctl restart dnsmasq

🔸 Step 4: Renew Client IP

On Client:

sudo dhclient -r
sudo dhclient


Check IP:

ifconfig


✅ Client will always get:

192.168.0.10
